review.body:
Thanks for your updates and apologies for reading things as a "naive user": You know everything about envoy (incl. standard usage of the image(s)) but not every reader of the documentation does  -- therefore links to further information would be most welcome to get one started looking at this documentation (or just looking at the docker hub entry to be generated at `openquantumsafe/envoy`).

> Please do add to the openquantumsafe docker! I have updated all lines to reference openquantumsafe/envoy or openquantumsafe/envoy:latest. I assume this doesn't exist yet, so it will throw an error until it does. For example, [here](https://github.com/drouhana/oqs-demos/blob/65cfd957b99b97524c7cc553f07b798d0cbcebac/envoy/tls/Dockerfile#L4)

Does this create a hen-and-egg situation? The CI job must be able to complete (and push the resultant image to dockerhub) before it already is there. Is this guaranteed with this setup (with the second Dockerfile in `tls`)? Apologies if this is clear in your eyes, but I still need to read up on `docker-compose` to understand how you intend it to behave. 

> I have also added to the .circlci. Please let me know if it is terrible and needs correcting, I tried to follow what the other entries had done for testing.

It looks basically OK -- with the caveat that `docker-compose` probably needs to be installed as per the documentation referenced in my comment at the code location.

Finally, did you run the `circle-ci` job added locally on your machine to ensure it runs OK when deploying? See the [how-to](https://circleci.com/docs/local-cli/).
